<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-21-0918 </DOCNO><TEXT>The methodical procedure for the improvement of methods and machinerytreats the development of operating equipment in view of systematic considerations- both as an isolated function and a component of a larger closed system.Each instrument or technology is limited to a certain degree of development.A review of the nearly exhausted development capabilities of the fullymechanized longwall face is presented. When development limits have beenreached, new methods or machinery should be developed with the help ofa methodical procedure, the essential principles of which are presented.Examples are included to illustrate this methodical development procedure.4 refs., 10 figs.</TEXT></DOC>